//create a class declaration
class Xyz:public superClass{

public:
	Xyz();//constuctor declaration do not put return type before it--common mistake

};
//--------------
//constructor declaration
Xyz::Xyz(){

};
-------------------------------------------
pointer to a class can be created in 2 ways

1.
Xyz foo ;
Xyz *pfoo=&foo;

Now 
pfoo->function();//access to the the object through the pointer

2.
Xyz* foo=new Xyz();
now foo is the pointer to the Xyz object
